Enum GuildProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GuildProperties>
      • com.Cardinal.CommandPackage.Handle.Properties.GuildProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GuildProperties>

    public enum GuildProperties
extends java.lang.Enum<GuildProperties>
    An enumeration of common properties that are different for each guild. The command package uses all these properties when processing events.
    Author:
    Cardinal System
    See Also:
    PropertiesHandler

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PREFIX

        public static final GuildProperties PREFIX
        Each guild can set a unique command prefix for that guild. This property marks the chosen prefix. Saved as a string.

      • COMMAND_ALIASES

        public static final GuildProperties COMMAND_ALIASES
        Each guild can set unique command aliases. This property marks the command aliases. Saved as a map with the structure:

        {"Alias": "Command"}

        Here is an example of an alias map serialized as a json object: 
                "aliases": {
                "h": "help",
                "k": "kick",
                "b": "ban"
        }

      • BOT_CHANNEL

        public static final GuildProperties BOT_CHANNEL
        Guilds have the option to set a bot channel. The bot will only listen in the bot channel. This is a channel ID, and is saved as a string.
